WEBVTT

00:00.016 --> 00:01.203
Synced and corrected by Dragoniod for
www.addic7ed.com

00:01.227 --> 00:02.760
- Arthur?
- Yeah?

00:02.762 --> 00:06.031
I may have just invented
a new taste sensation.

00:06.056 --> 00:06.993
Yeah, what is it, Tush?

00:07.063 --> 00:09.915
I take a donut hole, I put a
little coffee in the middle,

00:09.940 --> 00:12.729
I call it the Tush-hole.

00:14.096 --> 00:16.531
- I don't think that's a good idea...
- No, shh, shh. Let's just enjoy this.

00:16.556 --> 00:17.775
Yes?

00:17.777 --> 00:19.777
It doesn't have to be coffee, of course.

00:19.779 --> 00:22.313
You could put anything
in your Tush-hole.

00:23.415 --> 00:25.016
Hey, that could be our ad campaign.

00:25.018 --> 00:27.719
"What do you like in your Tush-hole"

00:28.551 --> 00:30.755
Oop, I just heard it. Never mind.

00:36.763 --> 00:37.662
Fawz, what's going on?

00:37.664 --> 00:39.397
My dry cleaners was robbed!

00:39.399 --> 00:40.798
- No!
- Are you okay?

00:40.800 --> 00:42.267
Those bastards took everything!

00:42.269 --> 00:44.235
My computers, my chemicals,

00:44.237 --> 00:47.272
my hangers that say,
"We Don't Use Chemicals."

00:48.340 --> 00:50.041
Cop, girl cop, come and help.

00:50.043 --> 00:51.543
Uh, girl cop's not going anywhere

00:51.545 --> 00:53.478
till she's had her coffee.

00:53.480 --> 00:55.947
In the last 24 hours,
we've had six break-ins,

00:55.949 --> 00:59.217
two muggings and one public urinator.

00:59.219 --> 01:02.187
I really had to go.

01:02.189 --> 01:05.256
Did I really have to watch?

01:05.257 --> 01:07.158
Uh, the coffee's still brewing.

01:07.160 --> 01:08.660
All right, it'll be a few more minutes.

01:08.662 --> 01:09.994
Fine. I'll be next door.

01:09.996 --> 01:12.174
I have to give the insurance
company my wish list.

01:12.199 --> 01:16.100
I mean, the list of
things that were stolen.

01:16.102 --> 01:18.155
This crime wave is hitting
close to home, ain't it?

01:18.187 --> 01:19.726
Yeah, what's been happening here?

01:19.751 --> 01:21.906
I thought this neighborhood was
supposed to be getting nicer.

01:21.908 --> 01:25.009
Well, a spike in crime is often
a byproduct of gentrification.

01:25.011 --> 01:29.013
As Biggie Smalls once said,
"More Money, More Problems."

01:29.015 --> 01:32.150
It's actually "Mo' Money, Mo' Problems."

01:32.704 --> 01:34.931
I'm not comfortable saying it that way.

01:36.522 --> 01:38.389
Yeah, the crime wave's gotten so bad,

01:38.391 --> 01:40.491
the department's bringing in
reinforcements to help out.

01:40.493 --> 01:42.060
Yay, great. More cops.

01:42.062 --> 01:43.161
You know what that means:

01:43.163 --> 01:45.997
- more pat downs.
- More business.

01:45.999 --> 01:49.500
All this crime, guess it's
time to bring out my bus face.

01:49.502 --> 01:52.203
Did you say "bus face"?

01:52.205 --> 01:54.672
Yeah, it's this face I use
on public transportation

01:54.674 --> 01:56.274
so people don't mess with me.

01:56.276 --> 01:57.475
Let's see it.

02:01.380 --> 02:02.413
Oh, that's so cute.

02:02.415 --> 02:03.581
Adorable.

02:03.583 --> 02:05.583
Like a constipated Disney princess.

02:07.932 --> 02:10.588
Maya, that face might
work out in the suburbs,

02:10.590 --> 02:12.190
but you're in Uptown now.

02:12.192 --> 02:14.525
If you want the creepos on
the bus to leave you alone,

02:14.527 --> 02:16.527
act like a crazy person.

02:16.529 --> 02:17.962
Please don't show her how.

02:17.964 --> 02:19.268
Let me show you how.

02:20.467 --> 02:23.134
I invented a character
I call Johnny Buggins.

02:23.136 --> 02:24.769
He has a voice like this.

02:24.771 --> 02:27.672
Oh, hello there, Mr. James.

02:27.674 --> 02:28.973
You have beautiful eyes.

02:28.975 --> 02:32.569
May I take one home
and feed it to my robot?

02:35.547 --> 02:37.448
I hate Johnny Buggins.

02:37.450 --> 02:39.250
Works every time.

02:39.252 --> 02:41.786
What is taking you so long?

02:41.788 --> 02:44.289
You two are like Cagney and Lazy.

02:45.157 --> 02:46.641
Starsky and Not Much.

02:47.494 --> 02:49.027
Law & Order another donut.

02:49.029 --> 02:50.595
Okay, we get it!

02:50.597 --> 02:52.463
All right, just... We'll be right here.

02:52.465 --> 02:53.185
Forget the coffee.

02:53.210 --> 02:54.766
- Give me some beans.
- Okay.

02:54.768 --> 02:56.267
What?

02:56.269 --> 02:58.803
- Sugar.
- Oh, yeah.

02:58.805 --> 03:00.872
Mm-hmm.

03:00.874 --> 03:03.107
- Cream.
- Damn.

03:05.611 --> 03:07.812
Come on, junior, let's roll.

03:07.814 --> 03:10.515
Oh! Just kicked in.

03:18.684 --> 03:20.525
- Yo, that club was so lit.
- Right?

03:20.527 --> 03:21.553
That girl was so into me.

03:21.578 --> 03:22.788
Yeah, man, but look, next time,

03:22.873 --> 03:24.592
can you not introduce me as your butler?

03:25.694 --> 03:27.565
Let me check on the store real quick.

03:30.936 --> 03:32.370
Arthur? Is that you?

03:32.372 --> 03:34.138
Oh, geez!

03:34.140 --> 03:35.707
What the hell you guys doing out here?

03:35.709 --> 03:37.155
Well, I thought with
everything going on,

03:37.210 --> 03:38.409
I would check on the store.

03:38.467 --> 03:39.538
It's 4:00 in the morning!

03:39.620 --> 03:41.446
Well, yeah, Sweatpants
and I, we just got back

03:41.448 --> 03:42.613
from this after-hours club.

03:42.615 --> 03:44.803
How do you dance in those tight pants?

03:44.828 --> 03:46.718
Oh, well, I'm more of a upper-body guy.

03:46.720 --> 03:47.719
I see.

03:47.721 --> 03:49.253
- And I'm strictly lower body.
- Yeah.

03:49.255 --> 03:51.556
Yeah. Well, an-anyway...

03:51.558 --> 03:52.990
- What? Oh, you want some?
- Hmm? Hmm?

03:52.992 --> 03:54.559
Hey, hey!

03:54.561 --> 03:55.626
- Hey, guys!
- Oh!

03:55.628 --> 03:57.363
- Huh? 
- I'm-a catch you later, man.

03:57.388 --> 03:58.763
- All right, man, be good.
- All right, see you.

03:58.765 --> 04:00.765
- All right.
- What are you doing out, huh?

04:00.767 --> 04:01.933
In your robe.

04:01.935 --> 04:03.167
On your way to a prizefight?

04:03.169 --> 04:04.202
No.

04:04.204 --> 04:06.003
I just go down the
block to the paper box

04:06.005 --> 04:07.472
and pick up a Sun-Times.

04:07.474 --> 04:10.508
What? That's, like,
four blocks away, man.

04:10.510 --> 04:12.610
Well, so what? I do it every morning.

04:12.612 --> 04:13.911
It's my routine.

04:13.913 --> 04:15.947
Arthur, you cannot be walking
around this neighborhood

04:15.949 --> 04:18.182
at this hour, man. People get mugged.

04:18.184 --> 04:19.916
One time, I got robbed right over there.

04:19.918 --> 04:22.086
Yeah, I know, that's
because you're a target.

04:22.088 --> 04:24.622
I mean, look at me, I
got nothing to steal.

04:25.306 --> 04:27.325
Well, except for that coin purse.

04:27.327 --> 04:29.370
Oh, wait, that's not a coin purse!

